title: Brooch
provenance: Collection of Mrs. Cadwallader Jones, mother of Mrs. Max Farrand; Gift of Gertrude Sampson
description: In the shape of a low, wide basket filled with a floral and foliate arrangement, composed of rose-cut diamonds set in silver and gold. Reverse features closed settings; double-pronged pin, the longer of which slips under c-clasp. Possibly originally part of a tiara or a hair ornament.
name: Brooch
